snippet: It is not clear whether the 5-year-old girl was alive when John Jonchuck threw her into the bay about 60 feet below the Sunshine Skyway bridge in St. Petersburg.
abstract: St Petersburg, Fla, police charge John Jonchuck with first-degree murder after he threw his 5-year-old daughter Phoebe off bridge into Tampa Bay following pursuit by police; child's body was recovered about a mile from bridge, and it is unknown if she was alive when she was thrown into bay.
lead_paragraph: It is not clear whether the 5-year-old girl was alive when John Jonchuck threw her into the bay about 60 feet below the Sunshine Skyway bridge in St. Petersburg.

headline.main: Florida: Man Charged With Tossing Daughter Into Bay
